The '''Sangihe lilac kingfisher''' ('''''Cittura sanghirensis''''') is a species of [[kingfisher]] in the genus ''[[Lilac kingfisher|Cittura]]'', [[Endemism|endemic]] to the lowlands of the [[Indonesia|Indonesian]] island of [[Sangihe Islands|Sangihe]]. It was previously considered a subspecies of the [[Sulawesi lilac kingfisher]] (''C. cyanotis''), but was split as a distinct species by the [[IUCN Red List]] and [[BirdLife International]] in 2014, and the [[International Ornithologists' Union|International Ornithological Congress]] and Clements followed suit in 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|title=IOC World Bird List 12.1|website=IOC World Bird List Datasets|language=en-US|doi=10.14344/ioc.ml.12.1}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Eaton|first=James A.|title=Birds of the Indonesian Archipelago: Greater Sundas and Wallacea|isbn=978-84-16728-44-2|oclc=1249090579}}</ref>

